# University Management System Database (SQL)

## Overview

The **University Management System Database** is a relational database project developed using SQL to simulate the core operations of a university environment. The system manages information related to students, teachers, departments, courses, enrollments, and attendance records.

This project demonstrates practical database design concepts, including table relationships, data integrity, normalization, joins, aggregate functions, subqueries, and views.

---

## Features

* Department Management
* Student Records Management
* Teacher Records Management
* Course Management
* Student Course Enrollment
* Attendance Tracking
* Department-wise Student Analysis
* Academic Performance Tracking
* SQL Views for Reporting
* Advanced Queries using Joins and Subqueries

---

## Database Schema

### Tables

| Table Name      | Description                        |
| --------------- | ---------------------------------- |
| University_Info | Stores university information      |
| Department      | Stores department details          |
| Student         | Stores student records             |
| Teacher         | Stores teacher records             |
| Courses         | Stores course information          |
| Enrollment      | Manages student-course enrollments |
| Attendance      | Tracks student attendance          |

---

## Relationships

* One Department can have many Students.
* One Department can have many Teachers.
* One Department can offer multiple Courses.
* One Student can enroll in multiple Courses.
* One Course can have multiple Students.
* Attendance records are maintained for each Student-Course combination.

